EchoFlow — licensing overview
=============================

EchoFlow is free and open source, permanently. Different parts of this
monorepo carry different licenses, chosen so that the client/protocol
surface is maximally reusable while the server cannot be re-hosted as a
closed commercial service by third parties:

  packages/protocol   MIT                 see packages/protocol/LICENSE
  apps/extension      MIT                 see apps/extension/LICENSE
  apps/backend        AGPL-3.0-only       see apps/backend/LICENSE

What this means in practice:

- Self-hosting is unrestricted. Run the backend on your own machine or
  server, for yourself, forever, at no cost. The AGPL places no
  obligations on private use.
- The wire protocol and the browser extension are MIT: build compatible
  clients or alternative backends freely.
- If you offer a modified backend to others over a network (e.g. as a
  hosted service), the AGPL requires you to publish your modifications
  under the same license.

Scripts, documentation, and other files not under the three package
directories above are MIT unless a file states otherwise.

Trademark: "EchoFlow" and any associated logos are not covered by the
licenses above. You may not use the name in a way that suggests your
distribution or service is official.

Contributions are accepted under the Developer Certificate of Origin —
see CONTRIBUTING.md.
